FORD COUNTY WIND FARM LLC
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Ford County Wind Farm LLC ("Ford County Wind") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Ford County, Illinois that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by Midcontinent Independent System Operator ("MISO"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Ford County Wind's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the MISO Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for MISO to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $448,000.00.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $448,000.00 / 12 = $37,333.33.
